The overall design is geometric and minimalist, characteristic of the De Stijl art movement. This style was prominent in the Netherlands during the early 20th century.

***End of description***

Who is the designer of the chair? <image 1>

The use of primary colors and geometric, minimalist design is characteristic of this movement. Therefore, the most likely nationality of the designer would be Dutch.

So, the answer is:

B. Dutch
